value.value: The carina which is present on the lateral margin of the mesoscutellum.
The pit that is located along the posterolateral margin of the mesoscutellum.

The hypopharyngeal muscle that arises from the distal end of the anterior tentorial arm or from the inner surface of the head capsule and inserts on the lateral surface of the proximolateral processes of the sitophore.
The procoxal muscle that arises from the cervical apodeme and inserts on the procoxa on the opposite side from which it arises.
The depression that is located laterally and proximally on abdominal tergum 2.
The apodeme that is located laterally on the postnotum.
The tergite that is located laterally on the abdominal tergum.
The appendage that is composed of the coxa and all distal leg segments and is connected to the pectus.
The segment that is part of a leg.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of the glossa and paraglossae.
The carina that extends along the lateral margin of the ventral propleural area.

label.value: longitudinal line of the dorsal profurcal lamella

value.value: The line that crosses the dorsal profurcal lamella and corresponds to the site of origin of the anterior profurcal lamella.
The carina that is longitudinal and is located on the metacoxa.

label.value: longitudinal muscle of the sucking pump

value.value: The epipharyngeal muscle that is unpaired and arises from the distal part of the pharyngeal wall and inserts along most of the length of the proximal epipharyngeal wall.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of abscissae extending along the long axis of the wing.
The area that is limited dorsally by the ventral margin of the antennal foramen laterally by the malar sulcus and ventrally by the oral foramen.
The anatomical line that is the shortest between the lower orbit and the ventrolateral margin of the cranium.
The sulcus that extends between the ventral margin of the compound eye and the base of the mandible.
The genitalia that is part of the male organism.

The appendage that is encircled by one sclerite that is connected to the cranium proximolaterally and to the maxillo-labial complex proximomedially via conjunctivae and articulates with the cranium via the anterior and posterior cranio-mandibular articulations.
The apodeme that corresponds to the site of insertion of the mandibular adductor muscle.
The condyle that is located ventrally (posteriorly) on the proximolateral edge of the mandible and inserts into the pleurostomal fossa.
The gland that opens mesally at the base of the mandible.
The line that delimits the periphery of an area.
The row of setae that is located along the margin of the wing blade in the same plane as the wing blade.
The abscissa that is located along the anterior margin of the fore wing and is thought to correspond to the anterior abscissa of the radius (R1).
The appendage that is encircled by the area that is proximally delimited by the hypostoma posteriorly, the median margin of the mandible laterally, the labrum anterolaterally and the labium medially.
The gland that opens medially at the bases of the maxillae.
The anatomical structure that is distal to the proximal margin of the first sclerite of the maxillary palp.
The male genitalia muscle that arises from the spiculum and inserts on the gonocondyle.
The gonossiculal muscle that arises ventromedially from the gonostyle/volsella complex and inserts laterally on the gonossiculus.
The impression that is longitudinal and located medially on the abdominal tergum 1.
The wing vein that is posterior to the radial vein and is connected to the anterior margin of the anterior median plate.
The area that is located between the notauli.

The mesotrochanteral muscle that arises from the ventral surface of the lateral mesofurcal arm medial to the site of origin of the lateral mesofurco-mesotrochanteral muscle and inserts on the mesotrochanteral apodeme.
The line that is located in the anteroposterior median line of the mesoscutum.
The sulcus that is a median mesoscutal line and that is adjacent to the (internal) median mesoscutal ridge.
The metacoxal muscle that arises from the paracoxal ridge and from the metadiscrimenal lamella and inserts anterolaterally on the dorsal margin of the metacoxa.
The depression that is oblique and located submedially on the mesopleuron between the fore coxa and posterolateral corner of the mesopleuron.
The ocellus that is located medially on the cranium.
The procoxal muscle that arises partly from the posteroventral surface of the ventral profurcal lamella and partly from the ventral surface of the profurcal arm.
The carina that is oriented anteroposteriorly and is located medially on the propodeum.
The sclerite that is located ventrally between the penisvalvae.
The sulcus that is located on the postgenal suture.
The cupulal muscle that arises medially from abdominal sternum 9 and inserts ventrolaterally on the cupula.
The area that is located posterolaterally and proximally on the coxa, proximal to the basicostal suture.
The inflection that extends along the dorsal margin of the mesopectus.
The ridge that extends along the posterior margin of the mesopectus.
The sulcus that extends along the posterior margin of the mesopectus, delimits the mesepimeral area and corresponds to the mesepimeral ridge.
The epimeron that is located on the mesopleuron.
